An outage on the PlayStation Network (PSN) is causing problems for gamers on PlayStation 4. Sony acknowledged the outage on its PSN Service Status page, with PlayStation Vue the only service fully operational at the time of writing. According to Sony, PSN is experiencing multiple issues, including gamers having difficulty signing in or creating an account, difficulty in launching games, applications, or online features, and difficulty accessing features and products on the PlayStation Store. “Our engineers are working to resolve the issue as soon as possible,” said Sony.